Review the ACL or filters for the routerâ€™s receive path and verify that only traffic sourced from the management network is allowed to access the router. This would include both management and control plane traffic.

Step 1: Verify that an inbound filter has been applied to loopback interface. This filter is used to restrict all traffic to the router engine. The interface configuration should look similar to the following: 
